7. EPFO Courtroom / Appeal Simulator

Target stakeholders: EPFO officers, employers, legal teams, trainees
Game format: Argument and decision-making simulator

The player handles quasi-judicial scenarios such as coverage disputes, contribution assessment, damages, interest, exemptions, and appeals.

Different players can take roles:

EPFO officer
Employer
Employee representative
Legal advisor
Appellate authority

Learning outcomes:

Officers learn principles of natural justice, evidence evaluation, speaking orders, and fair hearings. Employers learn compliance and legal consequences.

Example case:

“An establishment claims it has only 17 employees. Worker records suggest 23. Decide coverage after examining evidence.”

Gamification:

Order quality score, evidence score, natural justice score, appeal sustainability score.
